      "message": "Yes I remember. UBO size has a generally small limit (like 64KB), while SSBO size is generally unbounded (like 4GB). If you use a buffer that\u0027s huge, and bind a small part of it as UBO, that\u0027s expected to work. I recall binding the whole buffer failed something, since it was surpassing the Vulkan limit.\n\nWhat Jamie\u0027s change is doing is taking the min of the buffer size with `maxBoundBufferRange` which is the Vulkan limit for UBOs and SSBOs based on the call site, so the Vulkan requirement is satisfied.\n\nIn other words, `isStorageBuffer` is necessary, but it\u0027s implied by the caller\u0027s choice of `maxBoundBufferRange` :)",
